A collection of several tracts and discourses written in the years 1678, 1679, 1680, 1681, 1682, 1683, 1684, 1685 by Gilbert Burnet ; to which are added, a letter written to Dr. Burnet, giving an account of Cardinal Pool's secret power, the history of the power treason, with a vindication of the proceedings thereupon, an impartial consideration of the five Jesuits dying speeches, who were executed for the Popish Plot, 1679. Selections. 1685 Burnet, Gilbert, 1643-1715.
[6], 45, [3], 36, [2], 47 p.
Printed for Ric. Chiswell ..., London : 1685.
Reproduction of original in Huntington Library.
